  <Subject Subject_ID="300036799">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300212545</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>body armor for the head [300212545], body armor for neck and head [300205385], body armor [300036746], armor by form [300210822], armor (protective wear) [300036745], protective wear [300209266], costume by function [300212133], costume (mode of fashion) [300178802], Costume (hierarchy name) [300209261], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Open helmets usually forged in one piece, having at first an ogival-shaped skull, later a rounded one, which extended down to protect the cheeks, leaving a small opening for the face. They were in use from the mid-14th to the late 15th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Yelmo abierto, generalmente forjado en una única pieza, que en un principio tenía un casco en forma ogival, y, más tarde redondeada; se extiende hacia abajo para proteger las mejillas, dejando una pequeña abertura para la cara. Estuvieron en uso desde mediados del siglo XIV hasta finales del siglo XV.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Open helmen, meestal uit één stuk gesmeed, aanvankelijk met een ogivaalvormige, later met een ronde helmkap die ter bescherming doorliep tot de wangen, met een kleine opening voor het gezicht. Ze werden gebruikt van halverwege de 14e tot aan het eind van de 15e eeuw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052412/Wolters beeldwoordenboek (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>通常以一體成形方式鍛造的開放式頭盔，起初是尖頂拱形的頭罩，後來演變為圓形且向下延伸以保護臉頰，臉部只開一個小洞。這種頭盔於西元十四世紀中至十五世紀後期之間使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Offener, gewöhnlich in einem Stück geschmiedeter Helm, der zunächst eine spitzbogig geformte, später gerundete Helmglocke besitzt, die sich nach unten ausdehnt, um die Wangen zu schützen, und eine kleine Gesichtsöffnung freilässt. Er war von der Mitte des 14. bis zum späten 15. Jahrhundert im Gebrauch.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
